Description: Handheld Daemon Python library
 HHD (Handheld Daemon) provides a unified interface for handheld device
 hardware features on Linux, including:
  - TDP (Thermal Design Power) control
  - Controller remapping and emulation (DualSense, Xbox)
  - Fan curve management
  - Battery charge limit control
  - RGB LED control
 .
 This package installs the Python 3 library.

Package: hhd
Architecture: all
Depends:
 ${python3:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 python3-hhd (= ${binary:Version}),
 udev,
Description: Handheld Daemon system service
 HHD (Handheld Daemon) provides a unified interface for handheld device
 hardware features on Linux. This package installs the systemd service
 and udev rules required to run HHD as a system daemon.
 .
 Supported devices include: Lenovo Legion Go, ASUS ROG Ally, Steam Deck,
 and many other handheld gaming PCs.
